text: Irakli Kobakhidze (; born 25 September 1978) is a Georgian constitutional scholar and politician. He is the 16th and current prime minister of Georgia since February 2024. He was a member of the Georgian Parliament from 2016 to 2024. He was also the chairman of the Parliament of Georgia from 2016 to 2019. He was the chairman of Georgian Dream party from 2021 to 2024. ==References== Category:1978 births Category:Living people Category:Prime Ministers of Georgia Category:Current national leaders Category:Politicians from Tbilisi Category:Speakers of the Parliament of Georgia
